                                         CAPE TOWN - The grandmother of three-year-old Jaylin Alexander who was shot in the face is calling for the arrest of her shooter. The toddler was seriously wounded when a stray bullet hit her in the face. An emotional Wendaline Weely told Eyewitness News when they visited her at the hospital they could see she was in a lot of pain. Little Jaylin is currently in ICU and has a scheduled operation on Tuesday. The family remains hopeful she will make a full recovery. “If I think about it my tears start falling. What they (the shooters) did was very bad.”